summary: The sales volume of chocolate bars manufactured in the uk was approximately 40 thousand tons in 2018 , an increase of over eight thousand tons from 2017 . This constitutes a recovery of the production volume , which collapsed between 2008 and 2011 and fell by just under eighty percent , before it stagnated in the early 2010s . A stagnating market ? The corresponding developments in sales values give the same picture as above .
